      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SPARKLING SEA (7) has had six weeks off since a brave effort in the NSW Oaks, working from a wider barrier but sticking on for fifth. That was the only time she has been beaten in six tries at this circuit and distance. Smart filly who is nicely placed in this line-up. MYTH YOU ALREADY (4) did a good job to come from wider and finish second last week, beaten 1.5 metres. That was his first outing for six weeks so it should have improved him and he recorded back-to-back wins at this circuit and distance earlier in the campaign. Major player. LENNETH (9) cops a wide draw but had enough speed to lead and score by 4.4m at this circuit and distance last week. Can play a role again. SEASIDE DELIGHT (2) has been tackling higher-graded races in the country and is well served by a favourable draw.",
